This paper discusses the generalization properties of deep learning networks, which is a topic that falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the impact of network architecture on generalization, which is relevant to the sub-category of neural networks (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of deep learning for computer vision tasks, which is relevant to the sub-category of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the optimization of deep learning networks, which is relevant to the sub-category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses the behavior of fully-connected networks, which is relevant to the sub-category of systems and control (cs.SY).
